  <CaptionedBlock heading="Bringing a Puppy Home to an HDB Flat" imageAlt="Small breed puppy in an HDB flat living room" imageSrc={hdbLivingRoom} imagePosition="left" imageRotate="right">
    <p>HDB rules allow one dog of an approved breed, or an approved cross, per flat. Condo and landed property owners can keep up to three, subject to the property's own pet policy.</p>
    <p>Corgis and Shiba Inus are not on the standard HDB-approved list. We'll tell you this plainly if you're considering either, rather than let you find out after you've already fallen for a puppy.</p>
    <p>Cavapoo, Maltipoo, Maltese, Bichonpoo, Bichon Frise, Cavapoochon, Chihuahua, Cockapoo, and Mini Dachshund are commonly approved as small breeds or crosses, though it's worth checking <a href="/first-time-owners/hdb-breeds" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">the full HDB-approved breed list</a> and arranging dog licensing with us before you commit.</p>
  </CaptionedBlock>

  <ComparisonSplit
    heading="HDB Breed Approval Quick Check"
    headingAccent="Quick Check"
    subhead="A fast reference before you fall for a breed you can't keep in your flat."
    mode="table"
